<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-11-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="767" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">693.003/589</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Crane</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-11-08"><hi rend="italic">November 8,
                                        1920</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 62</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your
                                despatch No. 225 of September 20, 1920, enclosing a copy of your
                                communication to the Chinese Foreign Office objecting to the
                                enforcement at the present time of any time limitation on inward
                                Transit Passes in view of transportation difficulties in the Chinese
                                interior. The Department approves of your action in this matter.</p>
                            <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>